            <p>Miao He (何淼) provides <strong>full Mandarin family law services</strong> to Chinese-Canadian clients in Toronto and the Greater Toronto Area — no interpreter needed, direct communication in Mandarin. She holds dual licences from the Law Society of Ontario (#83315K) and the China Bar Association, handling cross-border assets, marriage contracts, and divorce litigation in complex cases.</p>
          </div>

          <h2>Chinese-Canadian Divorce in Toronto: Common Complexities</h2>
          <p>Toronto is home to one of Canada's largest Chinese-Canadian communities. Divorce cases within this community frequently involve cross-border assets, pre-immigration property held in China, offshore accounts, and other complex legal issues that differ significantly from standard Ontario divorce cases.</p>
          <p>Miao He holds dual licences in Ontario and China. She understands both legal systems deeply and is one of the very few lawyers who can handle cross-border Canada-China family law matters directly — without referring you elsewhere.</p>

          <h2>Areas of Practice</h2>
          <ul class="content-list">
            <li><strong>Divorce Litigation</strong> — litigation strategy, property division, Equalization</li>
            <li><strong>Child Custody</strong> — primary caregiver determination, parenting time, child support</li>
            <li><strong>Marriage Contract / Separation Agreement / Cohabitation Agreement</strong> — drafting, review, validity assessment</li>
            <li><strong>Cross-Border Assets</strong> — Chinese real estate, offshore accounts, global net family property calculation</li>
            <li><strong>Spousal &amp; Child Support</strong> — imputed income, variation applications</li>
            <li><strong>Mediation &amp; Arbitration</strong> — alternative dispute resolution strategy</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Why Choose Miao He</h2>
          <p>Mandarin service is not simply a language convenience — it means you do not need to explain your situation through an interpreter, no important detail is lost due to a language barrier, and no translation error can undermine your legal strategy. Miao He communicates directly with you in Mandarin, understands the cultural context of Chinese-Canadian families, and has direct expertise in the legal complexities of cross-border assets.</p>
          <p>The office is located in Markham, and Zoom consultations are available province-wide. Toronto clients do not need to travel far to receive a full-service consultation.</p>

          <div class="qa-block">
            <h3>Q: I am divorcing in Toronto but I still have property in China. Does the Canadian court have jurisdiction over that?</h3>
            <p>A: Yes. Ontario family law calculates Equalization based on <strong>global net family property</strong> — the value of property held in China is included and affects how Ontario assets are divided. Miao He holds dual licences in Ontario and China and can assist with cross-border asset matters directly. Call 647-930-6688.</p>
          </div>

